If A is a symmetric matrix and B is a skew-symmetric matrix such that A + B = $$\left[ {\matrix{
   2 &amp; 3  \cr 
   5 &amp; { - 1}  \cr 

 } } \right]$$, then AB is equal
to :

en.explanation:
$$A + B = \left[ {\matrix{
   2 &amp; 3  \cr 
   5 &amp; { - 1}  \cr 

 } } \right] = P(say)$$<br><br>
Now $$A = {{P + {P^T}} \over 2}\&amp; B = {{P - {P^T}} \over 2}$$<br><br>
So $$A = {1 \over 2}\left( {\left[ {\matrix{
   2 &amp; 3  \cr 
   5 &amp; { - 1}  \cr 

 } } \right] + \left[ {\matrix{
   2 &amp; 5  \cr 
   3 &amp; { - 1}  \cr 

 } } \right]} \right) = \left[ {\matrix{
   2 &amp; 4  \cr 
   4 &amp; { - 1}  \cr 

 } } \right]$$<br><br>
$$B = {1 \over 2}\left( {\left[ {\matrix{
   2 &amp; 3  \cr 
   5 &amp; { - 1}  \cr 

 } } \right] - \left[ {\matrix{
   2 &amp; 5  \cr 
   3 &amp; { - 1}  \cr 

 } } \right]} \right) = \left[ {\matrix{
   0 &amp; { - 1}  \cr 
   1 &amp; 0  \cr 

 } } \right]$$<br><br>
So $$AB = \left( {\left[ {\matrix{
   2 &amp; 4  \cr 
   4 &amp; { - 1}  \cr 

 } } \right]\left[ {\matrix{
   0 &amp; { - 1}  \cr 
   1 &amp; 0  \cr 

 } } \right]} \right) = \left[ {\matrix{
   4 &amp; { - 2}  \cr 
   { - 1} &amp; { - 4}  \cr 

 } } \right]$$

